description: in recognition of the extraordinary services they have rendered by their joint researches on the radiation phenomena discovered by Professor Henri Becquerel

name: Marie Curie, nee Sklodowska
description: in recognition of the extraordinary services they have rendered by their joint researches on the radiation phenomena discovered by Professor Henri Becquerel

name: Svante August Arrhenius
description: in recognition of the extraordinary services he has rendered to the advancement of chemistry by his electrolytic theory of dissociation

name: Ronald Ross
description: for his work on malaria, by which he has shown how it enters the organism and thereby has laid the foundation for successful research on this disease and methods of combating it

name: Hendrik Antoon Lorentz
description: in recognition of the extraordinary service they rendered by their researches into the influence of magnetism upon radiation phenomena

name: Pieter Zeeman
description: in recognition of the extraordinary service they rendered by their researches into the influence of magnetism upon radiation phenomena

name: Hermann Emil Fischer
description: in recognition of the extraordinary services he has rendered by his work on sugar and purine syntheses

name: Christian Matthias Theodor Mommsen
description: the greatest living master of the art of historical writing, with special reference to his monumental work, A history of Rome

name: Emil Adolf von Behring
description: for his work on serum therapy, especially its application against diphtheria, by which he has opened a new road in the domain of medical science and thereby placed in the hands of the physician a victorious weapon against illness and deaths

name: Jacobus Henricus van 't Hoff
description: in recognition of the extraordinary services he has rendered by the discovery of the laws of chemical dynamics and osmotic pressure in solutions

name: Wilhelm Conrad Rontgen
description: in recognition of the extraordinary services he has rendered by the discovery of the remarkable rays subsequently named after him

name: Sully Prudhomme
description: in special recognition of his poetic composition, which gives evidence of lofty idealism, artistic perfection and a rare combination of the qualities of both heart and intellect
